title: HTTP status 0 always labeled as timeout in non-Grok usage path
updated_at: "2026-07-15T04:43:52Z"
---
## Problem
`settleUsage` maps any `status === 0` to `API error (timeout)`. Network failures, aborts, and CORS-like failures also report status 0, so the UI mislabels them.

## Location
`contents/ui/ProfileController.qml` `settleUsage` (~status === 0 branch)

## Suggested fix
Track whether `ontimeout` fired (flag) vs generic status 0; show "timeout" only for the timeout path, else "network error" / "request failed".

## Source
Post-merge re-review nit of response-cache settleUsage